Scotland, the beginning of the 18th century. A dour young man dressed in black, raised to believe that he is one of GodÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢s elect and can do no wrong, stalks his brother through the dusky streets of Edinburgh. Filled with hatred and self-righteousness, he feels that his religion justifies any number of crimes, including murder.

